// HTTP module provides support for accessing inbound request headers as resource method arguments.
// The header key can be specified as variable name along with the `@http:Header` annotation or else can be specified
// in the `name` field of the annotation. The supported types are `string`, `string[]` and types can be optional.
// The type `string[]` returns the all values for given header key while `string` returns the first value. Unless the
// type is optional, request will be responded with 400 Bad request in the absence of the mentioned header.
// However, more header manipulations can be done via `http:Headers` header object which also can be accessed as
// resource method arguments without using the annotation.<br/><br/>
// For more information on the underlying module,
// see the [HTTP module](https://docs.central.ballerina.io/ballerina/http/latest/).
